defs.docs:
Laminar semi-reliable UDP protocol for multiplayer games. This library implements wraps around a UDP
 and provides light weight stream based interface that provides certain guarantees like reliability.

defs.name: field
defs.docs: We define "ack bitfield" such that each bit corresponds to acks of the 32 sequence numbers before "ack". So lets say "ack" is 100. If the first bit of "ack bitfield" is set, then the packet also includes an ack for packet 99. If the second bit is set, then packet 98 is acked. This goes all the way down to the 32nd bit for packet 68.

defs.name: set_nonblocking
defs.docs: Sets the blocking mode of the socket. In non-blocking mode, recv_from will not block if there is no data to be read. In blocking mode, it will. If using non-blocking mode, it is important to wait some amount of time between iterations, or it will quickly use all CPU available
